Hansda, a Zonal Commander, had a reward of Rs 10 lakh on his head. The joint operation by the COBRA battalion and district police also led to the recovery of weapons, including an SLR rifle.
title: Jharkhand: Hardcore Naxalite carrying Rs 10L bounty killed in Chaibasa

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: The clash over Community Notes is only the latest chapter in a bitter personal feud. Earlier this year, Navarro derided Musk as “a car assembler” whose supply chains depended on China. Musk retaliated with some of his harshest language yet, calling Navarro “dumber than a sack of bricks” and “truly a moron,” even mocking his Harvard PhD as “a bad thing.” He joked that Navarro should consult “Ron Vara” — the fictional expert Navarro once invented to bolster his anti-China arguments.
title: Why Elon Musk and India critic Peter Navarro detest each other

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: In Uttar Pradesh, an 11-year-old girl gave birth to a premature baby that tragically died shortly after delivery. Police have arrested Rashid, a 31-year-old man, accused of repeatedly raping and blackmailing her. The pregnancy was discovered when the girl complained of stomach pain, leading to an ultrasound revealing her condition.
title: 11-year-old delivers premature baby after repeated rape in Bareilly

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Amazon's stringent return-to-office mandate and location constraints are reportedly hindering its ability to attract top tech talent, particularly in high-demand areas like GenAI. Recruiters claim candidates are rejecting offers due to RTO requirements, even accepting lower salaries elsewhere for remote work.
title: Amazon’s hiring problem: RTO & more hurting AI roles; what recruiters said

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: In a Cricket World Cup League 2 match, Scotland defeated Canada. Scotland won the toss and chose to bowl. Canada's openers created an unwanted record by getting out on the first two balls. Brad Currie took five wickets. Shreyas Movva scored 60 runs, helping Canada reach 184. George Munsey's unbeaten 84 and Richie Berrington's 64 guided Scotland to victory.
title: First time in international cricket: Both openers dismissed in first two balls - How?

author: GLOBAL SPORTS DESK
description: Bill Belichick ignited a controversy by responding to UNC's decision to ban Patriots scouts. Belichick retaliated, barring UNC representatives from New England's facilities, emphasizing respect and fairness in college-NFL relations. His blunt statement resonated, highlighting the potential impact on scouting ties and turning a local issue into a national discussion about access and reciprocity.
title: 'It’s pretty simple': Bill Belichick’s blunt UNC ban verdict; shockwaves in college-NFL scouting

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: A deadly explosion struck a cricket match in Pakistan's Khyber Pakhtunkhwa, resulting in one fatality and multiple injuries. Police confirmed the attack in Bajaur district was targeted, utilizing an IED. The incident follows recent violent encounters in the province, highlighting ongoing security challenges as forces combat militant activities.
title: Terror strikes cricket ground in Pakistan: Explosion kills 1; several injured

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Vice President JD Vance is focused on his current role, deflecting questions about a potential 2028 presidential run. He emphasized the importance of performing well in his current position, suggesting that future political opportunities will arise naturally. Vance lauded Trump's tireless work ethic and his trust in his team, highlighting the collaborative nature of their partnership.
title: 'This may be most important job': Is Vance giving a hint about 2028 presidential run?

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: The potential imposition of US tariffs on software exports is causing apprehension in India's IT sector, which relies heavily on the US market. Experts warn this could lead to dual taxation and increased operational costs, exacerbating existing challenges from economic uncertainty and automation.
title: Trump tariffs on software exports? Indian IT sector worried - fears twin blows

author: VINOD KUMAR
description: Devastating floods in Punjab have significantly hampered efforts to expand the state's diminishing green cover, resulting in the loss of 4,94,956 trees across 776 hectares. With forest cover already low at 3.7% of its geographical area, the floods have deepened Punjab's ecological stress and caused an estimated damage of over Rs 360.5 lakh to the forest and wildlife preservation department.
title: Rain fury: Floods rip into Punjab's dwindling green cover, 5 lakh trees uprooted

description: Activist Sharjeel Imam has appealed to the Supreme Court against the Delhi High Court's denial of bail in a case related to the 2020 Delhi riots and anti-terror law. The High Court had rejected bail to several individuals, including Umar Khalid, emphasizing that protests cannot be a guise for conspiratorial violence.
title: Delhi riots: Sharjeel Imam moves Supreme Court against HC’s bail denial

author: GLOBAL SPORTS DESK
description: In a display of their ongoing rugby rivalry, Kate Middleton and Prince William attended separate Women's Rugby World Cup matches on September 6, 2025. Princess Kate, patron of the Rugby Football Union, cheered for England against Australia in East Sussex. Meanwhile, Prince William, patron of the Welsh Rugby Union, supported Wales in their match against Fiji in Exeter.
title: Kate and William split loyalties: Rival rugby outings; clash at Women’s World Cup

description: Sikandar Raza surpassed Virat Kohli's record for the most Player of the Match awards in T20Is, achieving his 17th during Zimbabwe's victory against Sri Lanka. Raza's impressive performance, including 3 wickets for 11 runs, helped restrict Sri Lanka to a mere 80 runs. This accomplishment places him ahead of Kohli and Suryakumar Yadav among full-member nations.

description: Iryna Zarutska, a 23-year-old Ukrainian refugee, was fatally stabbed on a Charlotte light rail train in a random attack. Brown has been charged with first-degree murder, raising concerns about transit safety and prompting increased security measures.

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Starlink is actively establishing its terrestrial infrastructure in India, engaging in advanced discussions with data center operators, internet exchange providers, and telecom companies. Having secured necessary clearances and trial bandwidth, Starlink is finalizing ground station locations to connect its satellite network. These strategic tie-ups aim to support large-scale satellite connectivity, positioning Starlink to compete in India's growing satcom market.

author: DISHANK PUROHIT
description: A Rajasthan government report reveals 20 custodial deaths in police lock-ups between August 2023 and August 2025, attributed to health issues, suicides, and one disputed case. Despite recurring patterns and procedural lapses, investigations have largely cleared police personnel, resulting in minor disciplinary actions. The Supreme Court is now examining compliance with CCTV mandates amid concerns over custodial deaths.
title: Rajasthan: 20 deaths in police lock-up in 2 years; govt report indicates a pattern

author: TNN
description: A nine-year-old's death in Tehatta, Nadia district, triggered a violent mob lynching. Swarnabha Mondal, missing since Friday, was found dead in a pond. Locals, suspecting Utpal and Soma Biswas due to a family feud, attacked their home, resulting in their deaths. Police inaction is alleged, with locals claiming quicker response could have prevented the tragedies. An investigation is underway.
title: 9-year-old’s body found in pond in West Bengal, mob lynch neighbours on suspicion

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Aryna Sabalenka overcame a late-set stumble to defeat Amanda Anisimova and secure her second consecutive US Open title. Sabalenka's victory marks her fourth Grand Slam title and a redemption after previous final losses. She celebrated with champagne, showcasing a relaxed champion who learned from past setbacks, while Anisimova acknowledged not fighting hard enough.
title: Aryna Sabalenka brings champagne to press conference after US Open win – Watch

author: KOUSHIKI SAHA
description: As the Yamuna River slowly recedes in Delhi, displaced families from low-lying areas face a difficult choice between safety and salvaging their belongings. Driven by the need to recover lost possessions, many risk returning to their flooded homes despite official warnings.
title: Delhi floods: Torn between relief camps and lost homes, families fight to survive

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: A massive immigration raid at a Hyundai plant in Georgia led to the arrest of 475 workers, predominantly Korean nationals, triggering diplomatic intervention from South Korea. Federal agents executed the operation following a months-long investigation into unlawful employment practices. The raid involved multiple agencies, highlighting a crackdown on workforce exploitation and federal law violations, as stated by Homeland Security.

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: A Robinson R66 helicopter crashed and caught fire near Airlake Airport in Minnesota on Saturday afternoon, resulting in no survivors. The crash occurred in a non-residential area, with the NTSB and FAA launching an investigation into the cause. The helicopter, which can seat up to five people, was found west of the airport.

author: TOI Education
description: NIRF 2025 rankings are under scrutiny as Banaras Hindu University's Faculty of Dental Sciences appears twice in the dental category, securing 15th and 18th positions. Conflicting data on placements further underscores the need for a methodology review to maintain credibility.

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Cristiano Ronaldo, at 40, showed his brilliance. He scored twice as Portugal defeated Armenia 5-0 in a World Cup qualifier. Ronaldo's goals increased his international record to 140. description: Ashwini Kumar, a Noida resident, was apprehended by Mumbai Police for making threatening calls about serial explosions in Mumbai, driven by a desire to avenge a former friend, Firoz Ahmed, who had previously filed a cheating case against him. Kumar falsely implicated Firoz in a terror plot, claiming 34 bombs were planted and Pakistani terrorists had infiltrated the city.

The ceremony, a highlight for basketball enthusiasts, will be broadcast live from Springfield, Massachusetts.

description: In Anuppur district, a shocking crime unfolded as Bhaiyalal Rajak was murdered by his third wife, Munni, and her lover, Narayan Das Kushwaha. The couple, along with an accomplice, bludgeoned Bhaiyalal to death with an iron rod before disposing of his body in a well.

description: Donald Trump is set to attend the US Open men's final, marking his first appearance since 2015. He will be watching from Rolex's suite, despite his administration's recent imposition of a 39% tariff on Swiss products. This visit adds to Trump's recent attendance at major sporting events, though ABC's broadcast may avoid showing any potential protests.

description: Kansas City Chiefs fans are anxious following reports of a potential shoulder dislocation for Xavier Worthy. A sports medicine specialist suggests a possible three-week recovery, but cautions about a high re-injury risk. Surgery, the worst-case scenario, could sideline Worthy for the season. His absence would force offensive adjustments, potentially impacting Mahomes and other receivers.

description: The FATF report commends India's online MLA portal for streamlining international cooperation in money laundering cases. description: Following the defacement of the national emblem at Srinagar's Hazratbal shrine, Ladakh LG Kavinder Gupta pledged strict action. description: Aryna Sabalenka defended her US Open crown in style, beating Amanda Anisimova 6-3, 7-6(3) for her fourth Grand Slam title and 100th major match win. The world No. 1 celebrated in a shimmering silver jacket that matched her trophy, blending grit with glamour on a rain-soaked New York night to become the first repeat champion since Serena Williams.

description: PM Modi and President Macron discussed the Ukraine conflict, with Macron briefing Modi on the Coalition of the Willing's meeting in Paris regarding security guarantees for Ukraine. author: TNN
description: A recent study by IITM reveals Delhi's air contains the highest mercury concentration among Indian cities, significantly exceeding global background levels. The study, spanning from 2018 to 2024, links the pollution to coal use, traffic, and industries. While Delhi's mercury levels are alarming, the research indicates a decline compared to previous years.

description: Following positive remarks from Donald Trump, PM Modi reciprocated, hinting at a potential turnaround in the strained India-US relationship. External Affairs Minister Jaishankar emphasized India's commitment to the partnership, raising prospects of a phone call between the leaders.

description: The Election Commission of India is set to conduct a nationwide Special Intensive Revision (SIR) of electoral rolls, mirroring the exercise recently held in Bihar. Scheduled to begin soon, this initiative aims to purify the rolls by removing ineligible voters and ensuring all eligible citizens are included.

author: TNN
description: Gurgaon police were left baffled after Poojan Prasad, presumed dead and cremated by his son, returned home a day later. Police had identified a mutilated body as Prasad based on a missing person report and family claims. The cremation took place before Prasad's brother-in-law spotted him alive.
